questions: Is it something created/manufactured by humans (as opposed to naturally occurring)?
Is it a living organism (or part of one)?
Is it an animal (as opposed to a plant, fungus, or microorganism)?
Is it a plant (as opposed to a fungus or microorganism)?
Is it a microorganism (like bacteria, archaea, or protist)?
Is it part of a larger organism (like an organ, tissue, or bodily structure)?
Is it part of an animal (as opposed to being part of a plant, fungus, or microorganism)?
Is it part of a plant?
Is it a reproductive part of a plant (flower, fruit, or seed)?
Is it a fruit (the structure that develops from a flower and contains seeds)?
Is it a commonly eaten fruit in most Western countries (as opposed to exotic or rarely consumed)?
Does this fruit grow on trees (as opposed to vines, bushes, or other plant structures)?
Is it typically larger than a tennis ball when fully grown?
Is it typically red when ripe?
